05:38.506 --> 05:39.840
You could make the argument

05:39.873 --> 05:41.809
that there is no better place
to eat in Europe

05:41.842 --> 05:44.978
than the city of San Sebastián.

05:45.012 --> 05:48.048
There are more Michelin starred
restaurants per capita here

05:48.081 --> 05:50.050
than anywhere on Earth.

05:50.083 --> 05:52.920
But even the everyday joints
are superb.

05:52.953 --> 05:54.254
The love of food,

05:54.287 --> 05:56.890
the insistence on
the very best ingredients,

05:56.924 --> 06:00.060
is fundamental to the culture
and to life here.

06:00.093 --> 06:01.929
And it's beautiful.

06:01.962 --> 06:03.163
Did I say that?

06:03.196 --> 06:05.332
It's a beautiful city.

06:56.917 --> 06:58.986
You know exactly
where to go, no?

06:59.019 --> 07:01.054
If I'm lost, I'm only lost
for two minutes.

07:01.088 --> 07:02.790
I always find my way.
You'll find it.

07:02.823 --> 07:04.224
- Oh, here he is.
- Eh?

07:04.257 --> 07:05.659
¿Qué tal?

07:05.693 --> 07:07.661
Juan Mari Arzak has been,
since I first met him

07:07.695 --> 07:10.330
and his amazing,
accomplished daughter Elena,

07:10.363 --> 07:11.999
my mentor and friend,

07:12.032 --> 07:15.503
steadfast and loyal
in every way a person can be.

07:15.536 --> 07:17.004
Father and daughter

07:17.037 --> 07:20.173
are two of the greatest chefs
in the world.

07:20.207 --> 07:22.743
Bueno.

07:22.776 --> 07:23.777
¿Qué tal?
Bien.

07:23.811 --> 07:24.845
You are happy.

07:24.878 --> 07:26.580
Very.
Très content.

07:26.614 --> 07:27.948
I love it here.

07:34.321 --> 07:38.191
